  "April 27, 1969",
  "",
  "Dear Ethel,",
  "",
  "I got a job as a nurse in a local hospital.",
  "Yay!",
  "I hope you can read the sarcasm in that word.",
  "",
  "Barb was right.",
  "They’re treating me like I’m a candy striper.",
  "Sometimes it makes me so mad I want to scream.",
  "They have me on the night shift, answering phones and changing bedpans and refilling water pitchers.",
